## I. THE CORE V — Triple-Combo Minimum Viable Interpretation

**The 4 logs every geologist needs:**

| Log | What it measures | Key output |
|-----|-----------------|------------|
| **GR** | Natural gamma radiation | Vsh (shale volume) via IGR |
| **RT** | Deep resistivity (ohm-m) | Sw (water saturation) via Archie |
| **RHOB** | Bulk density (g/cc) | PHIE (porosity) via density contrast |
| **NPHI** | Neutron porosity (fraction) | Gas detection via density-neutron crossover |

**Optional (confirmation quality):**
- SP → SP deflection for Rw estimation
- DT → Sonic for matrix type and compaction
- CAL → Washout detection (bad hole conditions)

