## III. The GEOXLogInterpreterTool

**File:** `src/domains/geophysics/logInterpreter.ts`

Input: `{ GR, RT, RHOB, NPHI, SP, DT, CAL, GR_clean, GR_shale, RW, matrix }`
Output:
- `Vsh[]` — volume of shale (Larionov corrected IGR)
- `PHIE[]` — effective porosity (density-neutron method, shale-corrected)
- `SW[]` — water saturation (Archie: Sw = (RW/RT)^(1/N) × φ^(-M/N))
- `BVW[]` — bulk volume of water = PHIE × SW
- `anomalyScore[]` — composite anomalous contrast A per sample
- `fluidFlag[]` — WATER / GAS / OIL / INDETERMINATE per sample
- `lithology[]` — SHALE / SANDSTONE / LIMESTONE / DOLOMITE / ANHYDRITE / COAL / DENSE_LIMESTONE
- `quality[]` — GOOD / FAIR / POOR per sample
- `anomalyContrast{}` — κGR, κRHOB, κNPHI, κRT, composite
- F8 uncertainty tag

